.TH TIX\-ISSUE 1 "February 2026" "tix" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
tix\-issue \- manage issues in the tix ticket system
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tix issue add
.I "description"
.br
.B tix issue done
.RI [ id ]
.br
.B tix issue done\-all
.br
.B tix issue done\-ids
.IR id1 " " id2 " ..."
.SH DESCRIPTION
Issues are bug reports and problems tracked alongside tasks.
Unlike tasks, issues have no lifecycle states\(emthey are either
open (pending) or resolved (deleted).
.PP
Issue IDs use the prefix
.BR I\- .
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.SS tix issue add \fI"description"\fR
Create a new issue.
The description must be non\-empty.
The author is auto\-filled from
.BR "git config user.name" .
.PP
.B Output:
.RS
.nf
{"id":"I\-XXXXXXXX","desc":"..."}
.fi
.RE
.SS tix issue done \fR[\fIid\fR]
Resolve a single issue.
If
.I id
is omitted, the first pending issue is resolved.
.PP
.B Output:
.RS
.nf
{"id":"I\-XXXXXXXX","status":"resolved"}
.fi
.RE
.SS tix issue done\-all
Resolve all pending issues at once.
.PP
.B Output:
.RS
.nf
{"resolved":N}
.fi
.RE
.SS tix issue done\-ids \fIid1\fR \fIid2\fR ...
Resolve specific issues by ID.
At least one ID is required.
IDs that cannot be resolved are silently skipped.
.PP
.B Output:
.RS
.nf
{"resolved":N}
.fi
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Command succeeded.
.TP
.B 1
Invalid arguments or no issues found.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR tix (1),
.BR tix\-task (1)
